cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on deep learning systems and their vulnerability to watermark removal attacks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the potential copyright infringement issues, which falls under the scope of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The proposed techniques for watermark removal involve image processing and data augmentation, which are relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of deep learning models, which is relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
